# Fixture Builder workstream

Read `.cursor/plans/HANDOFF-fixture-builder.md` before starting work. Git workflow: `.cursor/plans/AGENT-GIT-INSTRUCTIONS.md`.

## Branch and repo

- Repo: `REBUS-Industries/prism` — branch `feat/fixture-builder` only (never commit to `main`)
- Fixtures API: `REBUS-Industries/prism-fixtures-service` — feature branches off `main`
- Daily sync: `git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`

## Owned files (edit freely)

- `web/src/admin/pages/FixtureEditor.vue`, `FixtureGdtfDebug.vue`
- `web/src/admin/components/FixtureViewer.vue`, `FixturePartProperties.vue`, `FixturePartTree.vue`, `FixtureQuadPreview.vue`, `DatumEditor.vue`, `DmxModePanel.vue`, `IesUploader.vue`
- `web/src/admin/utils/fixtureAssembly.ts`, `fixtureTransform.ts`
- `prism-fixtures-service/src/**` when API/import changes are needed

## Do not edit (materials-editor workstream)

- `prism/server/**`, materials editor pages/components
- `server/src/db/schema.ts` and migrations (open an issue if schema change needed)

## Shared files — coordinate before merge

- `web/src/shared/api.ts` — add types at end of relevant block; announce in team chat
- `web/src/admin/App.vue` — routes/nav only when necessary; announce first

## Build and deploy (keep UI + API in sync)

- Pre-PR check: `cd web && npm run build`
- **Web only:** `gh workflow run web-image --repo REBUS-Industries/prism --ref feat/fixture-builder`
- **prism `server/**` changed** (rare — avoid): also `server-image` on `prism`
- **Fixtures API changed:** merge `prism-fixtures-service` PR; `fixtures-image` auto-runs on merge to `main`, or manually:
  `gh workflow run fixtures-image --repo REBUS-Industries/prism-fixtures-service --ref <branch>`
- Merge via `/prism-merge <PR#>` in #prism-dev; confirm **web-image** and **fixtures-image** deploy-dev completed when both repos changed
- Dev target: https://prism.rebus.industries

## Commit format

`feat|fix|chore(web): <description>` (fixtures-service: `feat:` / `fix:` without web scope)
